916 \\)\n\n3. Calculating \\( \\ln(r) \\):\n   - \\( 1003 \\cdot 1.6094 \\)\n   - Breaking it down: \\( 1000 \\cdot 1.6094 = 1609.4 \\) and \\( 3 \\cdot 1.6094 = 4.8282 \\)\n   - Total: \\( 1609.4 + 4.8282 = 1614.2282 \\)\n\nComparing these results:\n\n- \\( \\ln(r) \\approx 1614.23 \\)\n- \\( \\ln(p) \\approx 2085.54 \\)\n- \\( \\ln(q) \\approx 2203.79 \\)\n\nThus, the order from smallest to largest is \\( \\ln(r) < \\ln(p) < \\ln(q) \\), which means \\( r < p < q \\).\n\nTo verify, I also considered expressing each number with a common exponent of 1003. Noticing that:\n\n- \\( p = 2^{3009} = (2^3)^{1003} = 8^{1003} \\)\n- \\( q = 3^{2006} = (3^2)^{1003} = 9^{1003} \\)\n- \\( r = 5^{1003} \\)\n\nSince the bases 5, 8, and 9 are in ascending order, their powers with the same exponent will follow the same order. Therefore, \\( 5^{1003} < 8^{1003} < 9^{1003} \\), confirming that \\( r < p < q \\).\n\nBoth methods led to the same conclusion, so I'm confident the correct answer is:\n\n\\boxed{D}"}
