t least one even number.\n\nAh, that matches the previous result. So, that seems consistent. So, 72 is the correct number.\n\nAlternatively, to ensure I didn't make a mistake, let me try another approach.\n\nHow many triples have at least one 5 and at least one even number?\n\nThis is equal to the sum over k=1 to 3 of ["}
