ose how many numbers are multiples of 5. Since we need at least one, it can be 1, 2, or 3.\n\nFor each of these, we also need to make sure that at least one of the numbers is even.\n\nLet me elaborate.\n\nLet me denote:\n\nNumber of triples = sum over k=1 to 3 of [Number of ways to have exactly k multiples of 5, with at least one even in the entire triple].\n\nSo, for each k=1,2,3:\n\n- Choose k positions out of 3 to be multiples of 5.\n\n- Each of these k positions can be 5 or not? Wait, no. Because if we're choosing exactly k multiples of 5, then those positions are set"}
